p: Human virus HCoV-229E is one of the species in genus alphacoronavirus, and it is the first group. It is the first coronavirus, isolated from patients with upper respiratory tract infections in the 1965. Until late 2002, only 2 human coronaviruses were very well knownâ€“HCoV-229E and HCoV-OC43. HCoV-OC43 is from the genus betacoronavirus, and it is in the second group of coronaviruses. HCoV-OC43 also isolates from patients with upper respiratory tract infections.
